    public ShopFloorTraining(AppDbContext db, Dictionary<string, int> slugMap) : base(db, slugMap) { }

    public override async Task SeedAsync()
    {
        // ── Overview (Article) ───────────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Shop Floor Display Overview",
            Slug = "shop-floor-overview",
            Summary = "What the shop floor display is, how kiosk mode works, scan-based authentication, worker cards, and job actions.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 5,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 1,
            AppRoutes = """["/display/shop-floor"]""",
            Tags = """["shop-floor","kiosk","display","clock"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Shop Floor Display Overview\n\nThe Shop Floor Display is a full-screen kiosk interface designed for production environments. It runs at `/display/shop-floor` and provides a touch-friendly, always-on dashboard where workers can clock in/out, view their assigned jobs, start and stop timers, mark jobs complete, receive goods, and ship orders — all without navigating the main application.\n\n### Kiosk Mode\n\nThe shop floor display operates in kiosk mode — it is not part of the standard application layout. There is no sidebar, no toolbar, and no header navigation. The entire screen is dedicated to the shop floor interface. It is meant to run on a dedicated monitor or tablet mounted on the production floor.\n\nThe display auto-refreshes every 15 seconds to keep worker status and job data current. A live clock is shown in the header. Theme (light/dark) and font size are persisted to localStorage so the kiosk retains its settings across browser restarts.\n\n### Two Display Variants\n\nThere are two shop floor routes:\n- **`/display/shop-floor`** — the main shop floor display with a worker card grid, unassigned jobs section, upcoming events, and full action overlays (clock, timer, receiving, shipping)\n- **`/display/shop-floor/clock`** — a dedicated clock-in/clock-out kiosk with terminal setup, team filtering, and a simpler scan-first flow using the `BarcodeScanInputComponent` (focused input field)\n\nThe main display uses the global `ScannerService` (passive keyboard-wedge detection on the document), while the clock kiosk uses a focused barcode scan input component.\n\n### Authentication Flow\n\nThe shop floor display uses ephemeral authentication — no persistent login session. Workers authenticate for a single action, then the session is cleared automatically. There are two ways to authenticate:\n\n1. **Scan + PIN:** The worker scans their RFID badge or barcode. The system identifies the scan via the API (`/display/shop-floor/identify-scan`). If it matches an employee, a PIN overlay appears. The worker enters their numeric PIN (minimum 4 digits) and submits. After successful auth, the actions overlay appears.\n\n2. **Card Tap + Password:** The worker taps their name card on the main grid. A password overlay appears (not PIN — full password). After successful auth, the actions overlay appears.\n\nBoth flows use a phase-based state machine: `main → pin → actions → (job-select | receiving | shipping) → main`. Auto-dismiss timeouts prevent stale overlays:\n- PIN phase: 20 seconds before auto-cancel\n- Job selection phase: 15 seconds before auto-cancel\n- Actions phase: 30 seconds of inactivity before auto-logout\n\n### Worker Card Grid\n\nThe main dashboard shows all workers in a responsive grid. Each worker card is a horizontal layout with:\n- A left **status stripe** whose color indicates the worker's clock status (green for working, yellow for break/lunch, gray for clocked out)\n- An **avatar** with the worker's initials and color\n- The worker's **name** and **current status** (short label from ClockEventTypeService)\n- **Elapsed time** since the worker entered their current status (live-updating every second)\n- A list of **assigned jobs** (up to 4 visible, with a '+N more' overflow indicator), each showing the job number, title, stage color dot, and a timer icon if the job has an active timer\n\nWorker cards are interactive — tapping one enters the PIN/password phase. Cards also serve as drop targets for drag-and-drop job assignment from the unassigned jobs section.\n\n### Job Actions\n\nAfter authenticating, the worker sees their assigned jobs with action buttons:\n- **Start Timer** (`play_circle`) — begins tracking time against the selected job\n- **Stop Timer** (`stop_circle`) — stops the running timer\n- **Mark Complete** (`check_circle`) — moves the job to the next stage and logs completion\n\nBelow the jobs, **clock action buttons** are shown dynamically based on the worker's current status (from `ClockEventTypeService`). These include Clock In, Clock Out, Break, Lunch, and any custom clock event types configured in the admin.\n\n### Receiving and Shipping\n\nRole-gated dock actions appear after authentication:\n- **Receive Goods** — available to Admin, Manager, OfficeManager, Engineer, and ProductionWorker roles. Shows open purchase orders with receivable lines, quantity adjustment (+/- buttons), optional bin location selection, and a Receive All confirmation button.\n- **Ship Goods** — available to Admin, Manager, and OfficeManager roles. Shows pending/packed shipments, shipment detail with carrier and tracking info, a Print Packing Slip button, and a Mark Shipped confirmation button.\n\n### IsShopFloor Stage Filter\n\nNot all kanban stages appear on the shop floor. The `IsShopFloor` boolean flag on `TrackType` and `JobStage` entities controls which stages are visible. Only stages marked `IsShopFloor = true` show their jobs on the shop floor display. This filters out non-physical stages like quoting, invoicing, and payment.\n\n### Unassigned Jobs and Drag-and-Drop\n\nUnassigned jobs (jobs with no `assigneeId`) appear in a separate section below the worker grid. Each unassigned job card shows the job number, title, stage name, stage color dot, and priority. Cards are draggable — drag an unassigned job onto a worker card to assign it. After clock-in, if the worker has no assignments, a job picker overlay appears automatically (15-second timeout).\n\n### Upcoming Events\n\nThe shop floor display shows upcoming events (meetings, training sessions, safety events) loaded from the Events API. Each event card shows the type icon, title, start time, location, and a 'Required' badge if applicable.\n\n### Kiosk Settings\n\nThe header includes controls for:\n- **Font size** — increase/decrease buttons with 5 steps (12px, 14px, 16px, 18px, 20px), applied via CSS zoom. Persisted to localStorage as `sf-font-index`.\n- **Theme toggle** — switches between light and dark themes. Persisted to localStorage as `sf-theme`.\n- **Live clock** — displays current time in `HH:MM:SS` format, updating every second.\n- **Kiosk search bar** — a debounced search input (300ms, min 2 chars) that queries `/display/shop-floor/search` for jobs, parts, and other entities.\n\n### Barcode-Driven Inventory Actions\n\nScanning is not just for clocking in. When a **part barcode** is scanned, the same scan action overlay used on the dedicated Inventory Scan page (`/display/shop-floor/scan`) pops up here on the main display too, offering up to 8 inventory actions — Move, Count, Receive, Issue, Ship, Inspect, Job, and Return — scoped to that part. Scanning a **storage-location barcode** opens a Location View overlay listing everything in that bin (item, lot, quantity) so you can drill into any item's actions. See the Inventory Scan Station article for the full action set and multi-scan mode.\n\n### Reverse / Undo a Recent Scan\n\nMistakes happen — a part moved to the wrong bin, a count keyed in wrong. The shop floor display has a **Recent Scan Actions** (undo) panel that lists scan actions from the last **6 hours**. Each entry shows the time, who did it, the action, quantity, part, and from→to locations. Pressing **Reverse** on an entry opens a **PIN prompt**; a valid PIN authorizes the reversal, which backs out the underlying movement and marks the entry as 'Reversed'. This is a supervised correction (PIN-gated), not a silent undo. Already-reversed entries cannot be reversed again.\n\n### Daily Scan Log\n\nFor a fuller audit, the **Daily Scan Log** (`/display/shop-floor/scan-log`, also openable as a panel) is a read-only table of all scan activity for a chosen day. Filter by **date** and by **action type** (Move, Count, Receive, Ship, Issue), and a summary line tallies the day's activity (e.g. '12 scans today — 4 moves, 2 receives'). Reversed entries are flagged with a red 'Reversed' chip. Where the undo panel is the short 6-hour correction window, the Daily Scan Log is the durable record.","sections":[]}"""
        });

        // ── Walkthrough ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
